message: Texas Has Hired Its First-Ever Director of Human Trafficking Prevention. Kim Grabert, said she hoped to help multiple state agencies cooperate to help Texas trafficking victims.

data.description: Earlier this year, the Texas Tribune’s Sold Out series examined how state policies – including a severely underfunded child welfare system – failed to help child sex-trafficking victims. Since then…
data.title: Texas Has Hired Its First-Ever Director of Human Trafficking Prevention
